@@YWelcome to ACK!MUD TNG.@@N  Here is what you need to know to get started.

@@gTHE BASICS@@N

  This is a multiclass MUD.  Your character belongs to several classes at
  once.  Levels are gained manually — type @@cGAIN@@N to see which classes
  you can advance and what it costs in experience points.
  See also:  @@cHELP GAIN@@N   @@cHELP MULTI@@N

  @@cRecall@@N anytime to return to the Temple in Midgaard — it is free.
  There is no rent.  Type @@cSAVE@@N to save your character, @@cQUIT@@N to exit.
  There are no deathtraps.

@@gWHEN YOU DIE@@N

  Your corpse is transported to the Morgue of Moribound.  Only you can
  loot your own corpse.  Corpses decay over time — retrieve yours promptly.
  You lose half your experience points on death.
  See also:  @@cHELP DEATH@@N

@@gESSENTIAL COMMANDS@@N

  @@cSCORE@@N       — your stats, level, gold, and condition
  @@cWORTH@@N       — experience progress toward your next gain
  @@cINVENTORY@@N   — items you are carrying
  @@cEQUIPMENT@@N   — items you are wearing or holding
  @@cTRAIN@@N       — spend trains to raise base attributes
  @@cWHO@@N         — see who else is online
  @@cHELP <topic>@@N — look up anything

@@gCOLOR@@N

  Color is configurable.  Type @@cCOLOUR HELP@@N to see available colors and
  how to set them.  Use @@cCONFIG@@N to toggle ANSI color on or off.
  See also:  @@cHELP COLOUR@@N

@@gCOMMUNICATION@@N

  @@cSAY <text>@@N      — speak to people in your room
  @@cGOSSIP <text>@@N   — public channel heard by everyone
  @@cTELL <name> <text>@@N — private message to one player
  @@cYELL <text>@@N     — heard in adjacent rooms
  @@cAFK@@N            — flag yourself as away from keyboard

@@gRULES@@N

  Type @@cHELP RULES@@N before you do anything else.  They are short.

@@gASKING FOR HELP@@N

  Use @@cGOSSIP@@N or @@cTELL@@N to ask other players questions.
  Immortals are staff — address them politely and only when needed.
  Use the @@cPRAY@@N command for genuine staff attention; do not spam it.
